          <blockquote>
            <h3 style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <a name="Core_Raiding_Rules">
            <span style="font-size: 18.0pt; color: #3E8AE0">Core Raiding Rules</span></a></h3>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Have Your Own Means 
            of Egress</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <b><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">We usually do not have a wizard.&nbsp; We 
            seldom have enough druids.&nbsp; Adding to that, there are unexpected 
            thing like server crashes, power outages, ISP outages, prolonged 
            LD.&nbsp; You get the point.&nbsp; Gate potions are cheap and easy.<b>&nbsp; <i>It 
            is better to have a gate potion and never use it then to be stuck 
            somewhere with no way out.</i></b></span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            &nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Be On Time</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><span style="color: black">For scheduled raids, make your own 
            arrangements for transportation to the raid site.&nbsp; If time is tight, 
            do it the day before the raid.&nbsp; Its ok to ask in guild chats for a 
            port, but do not get upset if no one can come get you.<br>
            </span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Reduce Spam</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            Please s</span><span style="color: black">pam as little as 
            possible.&nbsp; Ask for buffs with tells. &nbsp;Talk to friends in tells.&nbsp; Do 
            not send tells to the puller or RL asking them to pull &quot;your&quot; mob.&nbsp; 
            Stay off /OOC and shout.&nbsp; If you wish to, you can set up your own 
            spam channel.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            <br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Group Leaders 
            Are To Keep Track Of Their Group</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">Let someone know if you have a LD or AFK 
            person.&nbsp; As group leader, this is your job.&nbsp; In addition, let the 
            person handling the grouping know if someone left the raid.&nbsp; <i>DO 
            NOT</i> start picking up people on your own.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            <br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Pay Attention</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">Missing something sometimes means all the 
            difference between a narrow escape and a wipe.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            <br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Be Respectful 
            Of Grouping</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">Do not whine about your group.&nbsp; It is ok 
            to ask if the group maker realized you do not have a healer.&nbsp; It is 
            not ok to go on constantly because you do not have a cleric.&nbsp; Hate 
            raids have been run without a cleric in the past.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            <br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Death Happens</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">Do not come if you cannot afford to die.&nbsp; 
            We all die at raids.&nbsp; We have never lost a corpse yet.&nbsp; We have not 
            missed a Rez since our first epic attempt.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: #CC6600"><br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Stand Still</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">If you are not absolutely sure where you 
            are going, then stand still.&nbsp; It’s a lot easier to find you if your 
            where we were, versus where ever you happened to run off to.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;
            <br>
            <br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Control the 
            Buffing</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">Never heal or buff a FD puller unless he 
            knows you are doing it, and okays it.&nbsp; Otherwise, you will pick up 
            his aggro and if he FD's the camp will be trained or you will be 
            summoned.&nbsp; Alternatively, DT'ed in the case of Fear.<br>
            </span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Loot 
            Categories</font></span></b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2"><br>
            </font></span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><a name="Greed_Roll"><b><span style="color: #3E8AE0">Greed 
            Roll</span></b></a><span style="color: black"> - in which everyone 
            rolls, and does with the item as they wish.</span><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black"><br>
            <br>
            </span><b><u><span style="color: black">Can and Will Use</span></u></b><span style="color: black"> 
            - If the raid leader calls a <i>Can and Will Use </i>roll then 
            characters attending the raid roll if it is an upgrade for them.&nbsp; 
            Because not everyone at a raid rolls for this, these items won are 
            not to be sold or given to alts.&nbsp; One possible exception to this is 
            if you are using the item you won to trade up to an even better 
            item.&nbsp; You were given the item to make the character attending the 
            raid do a better job.&nbsp; The exception to the attendance rule is when 
            the raid leader asks you to bring a specific character and you get 
            permission to roll for the character you wanted to bring, and then 
            you can roll only that character.<br>
            <br>
            Mains roll level x 10 to 1000 and Bots roll 1 to 1000.<BR><BR>Alternates cannot roll unless all Mains and Bots pass. A person who is botting only gets one roll, they decide whether to roll for their Main or Bot (assuming both can use) and whoever wins must loot (meaning a Main can't using the Main rolling numbers and let their Bot loot). If a botter wins something with either their Main or their Bot then that counts as their win for both.<br>
            <br>
            <b><u>Camped and Reserved Loot</u></b> - In some cases, Loot may be 
            reserved.&nbsp; Including but not limited to this are epic drops, camped 
            rare spawns and upper extreme items like Breast Plates.&nbsp; In the case 
            of camped spawns, normally only the &quot;key&quot; item will be reserved.<br>
            <br>
            <b><u>Cash Loot</u></b> - This goes to the guild to cover cost 
            involved in raiding.<br>
            &nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Have Fun</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="font-size: 8.5pt; color: black">&nbsp;</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5; margin-bottom: .0001pt">
            <span style="color: black">You can be organized and have fun.&nbsp; If 
            fact a well run raid is tons more fun than chaos.&nbsp; The loots much 
            better too.</span></p>
            <h2 style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">&nbsp;</span></h2>
            <h2 style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5"><a name="Loot_Rules">
            <span style="color: #3E8AE0">Loot Rules</span></a></h2>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5"><b>
            <span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Who Can Roll</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">1.) You may only roll if you are a full 
            member of DP, not a probate. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">2.) You may only roll if you <i>CAN</i> 
            and <i>WILL</i> use the item.&nbsp; If you have equivalent or better 
            gear, you should pass.&nbsp; It is <i>HIGHLY</i> recommended you do some 
            research on common drops in a zone we are raiding so you will know 
            what gear there will be an upgrade for you. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">3.) Do not roll on an item with the 
            intent of selling it unless the raid leader announces a
            <a style="color: #3E8AE0; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none; text-line-through: none" href="http://www.divineprophecy.org/Info/raids.asp#Greed_Roll"> <i>
            GREED ROLL</i>.</a></span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">4.) Do not roll for an alt that is not on 
            the raid unless you were specifically requested to play your main 
            instead of your alt by the raid leader, and he has agreed you may 
            roll for the alt instead.</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">5.) Botted alts being used on the raid 
            are allowed to roll for items they can and will use.&nbsp; This assumes 
            the bot is actually contributing to the raid and not just along for 
            the ride.</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">6.) Regardless of how many characters you 
            are playing (botting), you will only get one roll per item at a raid 
            (you choose who rolls).&nbsp; If any of your characters win something, 
            you are not allowed to roll on anything else until everybody else 
            wins something or the raid leader makes an exception.</span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="font-size: 10.0pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">How to Roll</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">1.) Do not roll until the raid leader 
            calls for it.&nbsp; Rolling early will invalidate your roll and you may 
            not be allowed a second one on that item.&nbsp; Repeated violations could 
            mean no more rolls for you at all on that raid. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">2.) Random 10 X level to 1000 for Mains and 1 to 1000 for Bots.&nbsp; If you 
            random incorrectly you MUST roll again even if you like the result 
            of the incorrect roll.&nbsp; It is highly recommended you create a hotkey 
            for randoming. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">3.) Do not spam rolls or roll &quot;for the 
            fun of it&quot; on an item, you will not or cannot use.&nbsp; It is often 
            difficult to get all randoming done before items rot, and frivolous 
            rolls compound the problem. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="font-size: 10.0pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">If You Win</font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">1.) You may not roll on another item on 
            that raid until all in your class have won something.&nbsp; There may be 
            some exceptions allowed by the raid leader for differing types of 
            items. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">2.) Passing down items you are no longer 
            going to use to other guild members is a nice gesture, especially if 
            the item is something you won on a previous guild raid. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="font-size: 10.0pt; color: black"><br>
            </span><b><span style="color: #003399"><font size="2">Exceptional 
            Items </font></span></b></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">1.) Some loot will not be rolled on at 
            all but will be distributed by the officers.&nbsp; Common examples are 
            epic items, uber spells, reserved items, and so on. </span></p>
            <p style="line-height: 150%; margin-top: 5">
            <span style="color: black">2.) If someone has camped a mob 
            specifically waiting for it to pop (such as Lodizal) he or she may 
            reserve the key item from that mob, but other loot will be subject 
            to the above rules</span></p>
